<TEXT>
an advocacy group for the deaf sued state 
education officials monday alleging the states teacher 
certification test discriminates against deaf people 
the lawsuit filed in travis county state district court is the 
first challenge in the nation by deaf educators of a teacher 
certification exam the group said 
one of the plaintiffs nancy mumme 32 said the test asks 
questions about how to instruct students on the differences in the 
sound of certain letters 
how am i supposed to be identifying a sound ms mumme said 
in sign language through an interpreter 
the lawsuit against the texas education agency and state board 
of education says deaf people who want to become teachers shouldnt 
have to take the test until it has been adjusted 
the lawsuit was filed by the texas association of the deaf and 
ms mumme 
jorjanna price a spokeswoman for the education agency said 
lawyers for the agency had yet to see the lawsuit 
she said education commissioner wn kirby has met with deaf 
educators he said he wanted to look into the test matter ms 
price said 
ms mumme who has a maryland teaching certificate failed the 
texas test twice 
despite favorable evaluations and performance as a classroom 
teacher she was demoted last year and her contract at the texas 
school for the deaf has been canceled for this school year 
according to the lawsuit 
i have been very very frustrated i cried and cried after i 
got my test results back she said in an emotional statement at a 
news conference 
</TEXT>
