<TEXT>
arabs at seafront coffee shops have 
stopped talking about soccer and turned their attention to the 
persian gulf crisis and the american role in the middle east 
puffing at water pipes in the cafes of this island state that 
has become a banking and business center arabs from bahrain saudi 
arabia egypt and elsewhere gather to endlessly discuss the iraqi 
invasion of kuwait the american response and where it all will 
lead 
americas image in the arab world is 70 percent bright these 
days merchant abdullah ahmed suggested but this will not 
remain so in the fullness of tie of proisraeli 
america will surface again once the kuwait crisis is over 
listeners in white dishidasha gowns and kaffiyeh headgear nodded 
approvalme the ugly fac 
dont tell me that saudi arabian king fahd brought the 
americans to the persian gulf waters and the sacred land said 
one 
not at all ahmed responded saddam did but in the thick 
fog of arab politics well hear many different versions to the 
same story truth can easily be camouflaged 
lawyer mohammed adel interjected loudly no no no first of 
all lets define the basic elements of our discussion to gain 
clarity and avoid moving i four all supposed warlike scenarios are 
frightening and lots of innocent blood might be shed and someone 
will likely be blamed for this besides if israel gets involved in 
any military action against saddam all his arab adversaries would 
look very very bad and his sins be forgotten 
a number of religious men fingering worry beads shouted 
expressions of disapproval one mosque keeper interjected we go 
by the book of allah and say that fahd is struggling with a clean 
heart while saddam resists with a dirty mind 
the loudspeaker blared an egyptian song about arab unity garage 
owner ali juma had to raise his voice when he said the kuwaitis 
may have have been moneyminded but it is their money anyway and 
no one has any right to blame them for investing it in whatever 
manner they deem best for themselves 
many people in the gulf consider kuwaitis moneyminded and 
they are widely considered clever investors and sharp traders 
abdullah ahmed clapped and the waiter replaced the burned out 
tobacco in his water pipe inhaling smoke he said i believe the 
real crisis is yet to unfold what we see now is merely a spark 
the harm is done regardless of how the crisis will be ended 
the garage man said saddams mistake rests really with the 
enormity of his overblown reaction to kuwaits economic affronts 
instead of pulling kuwaiti ears he punched into their houses raped 
their women deflowered their daughters and looted their jewelry 
and i say the real crisis will unfold when the poor arabs 
begin to demand financial help from the rich arabs said ahmed 
sometimes peacefully and sometimes by force 
and saddam 
one eventuality envisions the iraqi people brightening their 
image and getting rid of saddam said ahmed but he also spoke of 
an alternative that saw an antiiraq economic blockade persisting 
and saddams machinations succeeding in stirring the arab masses 
against one government or another thus giving him a broader 
popularity and support 
another posibility he said was that the americans might 
provoke a fight and usher in the israelis which means saddam would 
die and become an arab martyr 
the lawyer summed it up 
i told you the future is bleak he said there are 
several options the sweetest of which is bitter 
