<TEXT>
following are excerpts of iraqi president 
saddam husseins message sunday to the families of westerners 
stranded in kuwait and iraq his remarks were carried by the 
official iraqi media and translated by the associated press 
ladies and gentlemen dear children 
i know that you are pained because your relatives are not 
allowed to leave iraq i am just as pained as you are i am fully 
convinced that the speaker and members of the iraqi national 
council are also pained and so are all iraqis and arabs 
we are all sorry for what happened it was not of our own 
making but the outcome of the will of certain people who acted 
arbitrarily and deviated from the will and teachings of god the 
responsibility for all this lies directly with us administration 
and the british government 
gentlemen you may not know that this country whose rulers 
concocted plots kuwait was part of iraq until 1913 and that iraq 
did not recognize it until the 1960s that the iraqi prime minister 
issued a decision in 1961 annexing kuwait turning it once again 
into a district linked to albasrah and appointing its sheikh as 
governor as was the case before world war i 
why do the us president and the british prime minister want to 
starve the iraqi people to death cursed be what they are doing 
what have the iraqi people done other than unite themselves and the 
families that were divided by circumstances in iraq and kuwait 
defend themselves and help oust the backward kuwaiti sheikh whose 
only concern was collecting money and women 
why are they imposing a siege on iraq to kill the babies and 
elderly as well as those who cannot get food and medicine why 
are they massing naval fleets squadrons of planes and ground 
forces with which they want to attack iraq 
as it is clear to you our homeland is being threatened by 
america and britain and those frustrated and humiliated ones 
involved with them our people are exposed to a grave danger 
it has been decided that preventing the foreigners from 
traveling outside iraq will open a deep dialogue with the 
peoples of those countries and those who represent them and with 
the administrations of those countries to find a peaceful solution 
and avert a catastrophe in the region and maybe the whole world 
 
the presence of the foreigners with the iraqi families at vital 
targets might prevent an attack 
we are seeking to deter the harm of death murder and 
starvation resulting from the us policy preventing their 
departure is a service to humanity 
i add ladies and gentlemen that many of iraqs children and 
your children will become orphans many of our women and your women 
will be widowed and many of our men and your men will die if war 
breaks out 
to deprive an individual from seeing his homeland for some time 
is better for him and for humanity as a whole than depriving 
thousands of people of life 
let us cooperate to prevent these governments from committing 
major crimes and force them to withdraw their troops from the 
region the presence of which may cause an intentional or 
unintentional spark that will result in an inferno and 
insurmountable flood of fire 
in order to give everybody the opportunity to achieve peace in 
order to disclose and expose those who want war and destruction 
and in order to secure freedom for all we put forward the 
following initiative 
firstly the security council with the consent of the united 
states guarantees that us forces will withdraw from the region 
under a fixed timetable and within a period not exceeding the time 
it took to mobilize them 
in addition the security council reassures saudi arabia that it 
will undertake collective military action against iraq if it 
attacks saudi arabia 
at the same time both iraq and saudi arabia pledge that neither 
of them will commit an act of aggression against the other or harm 
the interests of the other 
secondly the security council guarantees the security and 
stability in the entire region in accordance with the general basis 
contained in our previous initiative this alternative as we 
see it is the option to achieve full and comprehensive peace and 
bring definite stability to the region and the world 
thirdly if either paragraph one or two above is accomplished 
the foreigners shall be allowed to travel immediately as they 
choose 
fourthly if the above is not to be fulfilled for any acceptable 
reason then we will be content with a clear unequivocal written 
commitment from the us president that he withdraw his forces and 
those of his allies in accordance with a specific timetable and 
in a period that does not exceed the time to mobilize these forces 
that he pledges not to use force against iraq that he declares his 
respect for international law and refrain from violating it that 
he breaks the economic blockade on iraq by all sides immediately 
and that he deals with iraq on the basis of mutual respect and 
reciprocal refraining from harming the interests of either party 
for us when the above mentioned items are met we will use our 
constitutional powers to allow the foreigners concerned to travel 
out of iraq each according to his wish and decision 
fifthly the issue of kuwait should be left for the arabs to 
tackle as an arab issue the same way they handled similar issues 
such as that of the sahara in the arab maghreb region between 
morocco and the other parties concerned and the issue of syrias 
occupation of lebanon 
will the deaf hear this is a question directed to the us 
administration a correct answer to this question will serve 
humanity gods peace and blessings be upon you 
