<TEXT>
midwest corn fields are getting a chance 
to pinch hit for middle east oil fields 
the us energy department has recommended steppedup production 
of ethanol a cornbased moonshine that is blended with gasoline to 
make cleanerburning gasohol 
the call for more ethanol is part of a scramble to ease the loss 
of middle east oil arising from iraqs invasion of kuwait this 
month gasohol is approved for use in most vehicles and proponents 
say its time has come 
theres no question in my mind its the logical thing to do 
said wayne ryan who raises corn near wapello in southeastern iowa 
since ethanol was introduced in 1978 more than 800 million 
miles have been traveled using ethanol blends according to the 
iowa corn promotion board gasohol is 10 percent ethanol 
every year theres a new crop but every time you take a 
barrel of oil out of a domestic oil well it is closer to running 
dry said marty andreas a vice president at 
archerdanielsmidland co adm of decatur ill the nations 
largest ethanol processor 
a bushel of corn produces about 2 gallons of ethanol last 
year about 1 billion gallons of ethanol were produced nationwide 
from more than 360 million bushels of corn 
the government estimates us farmers will harvest 785 billion 
bushels of corn this fall one out of every five bushels will come 
from iowa the nations leading corn producer 
its renewable its domestic and ethanol is benign andreas 
said 
he said the energy department on wednesday asked ethanol 
industry officials how much idle capacity could be brought into 
production and was told that an additional 150 million to 175 
million gallons could be produced each year 
despite the increase in gasohol interest some warn that ethanol 
cannot shoulder the nations fuel burden 
the 1 billion gallons of ethanol produced last year compares 
with 115 billion gallons of gasoline consumed in the united states 
said david zinanon vice president of petroleum industries research 
associates a new york consulting firm 
even if ethanol production rises substantially in the years 
ahead it will remain only a small part of the us energy picture 
he said 
still ethanol has a strong cadre of supporters who list its 
benefits 
increased reliance on domestic fuels would help shrink the 
nations trade deficit and its dependence on foreign suppliers the 
united states imports more than half its oil in the first five 
months of 1990 iraq accounted for 74 percent of us oil imports 
according to the american petroleum institute 
with 10 percent ethanol gasoline burns cleaner reducing 
hazardous emissions of carbon monoxide the government said 
arizona colorado new mexico and nevada have programs that rely on 
ethanol blends to reduce pollution 
a major byproduct of ethanol production is corn gluten feed a 
protein supplement for livestock feed that is in demand at home and 
abroad 
andreas said the industry needs an extension in federal tax 
subsidies to maintain what has been a marginally profitable 
business 
the tax break forgives 6 cents of a 9cent federal excise tax on 
each gallon of ethanol sold by an oil company the subsidy is set 
to expire in three years 
rg ensz a spokesman for the american petroleum institute 
said ethanol production is not profitable without the tax break he 
added that studies disagree on whether ethanol production is 
energyefficient 
he said the energy used in transporting and processing the fuel 
together with the fuel used by tractors and other equipment in 
working the corn fields can use up as much energy as you make 
but ryan said he uses 23 gallons of diesel and some petroleum in 
nitrogen fertilizer to cultivate and harvest each acre which 
brings enough corn to produce 250 to 300 gallons of ethanol 
