refused to give his name 
the incident last wednesday night began with a double murder in 
which two people were shot to death during a romantic dispute 
police said 
the suspect fled and police in fengtai a suburb in southwest 
beijing were ordered to set up roadblocks 
at 1145 pm ma left his motherinlaws home in fengtai 
where he had gone to pick up his wife 
police said he was speeding when he came to the roadblock at an 
overpass just south of his motherinlaws home and ignored a 
police officer who motioned him to stop 
according to police the officer did not see that the van had 
diplomatic license plates the police also said the officer was 
aiming at the lower right side of the van when he fired but hit 
the rear windshield instead because the vehicle was going downhill 
police said the case was under investigation 
us embassy spokesman sherry bell said we regret the loss of 
life a tragic event but its certainly not an event thats 
going to affect sinous relations 
he said ma one of several dispatchers at the embassy had 
worked there almost 10 years bell said he was unaware of previous 
problems with ma 
many foreigners in beijing who employ drivers complain that the 
drivers often take the vehicles for personal use 
