<TEXT>
nasa said monday it will try to 
launch the newly repaired columbia on sept 1 more than three 
months after a hydrogen leak grounded the shuttle 
columbia will carry the astro observatory and the mission will 
be the first shuttle flight in five years devoted entirely to 
scientific research 
it also will be the first shuttle flight since april when 
discovery carried the flawed hubble space telescope into orbit 
columbias fuel leak followed by discovery of a similar problem 
with atlantis prompted the space agency to temporarily ground the 
entire shuttle fleet in june 
columbia will carry seven astronauts four of whom are 
astronomers and will operate the 150 million astro observatory 
three of the observatorys scientific instruments will study 
ultraviolet light emitted by stars and other objects the fourth 
instrument will examine cosmic sources of xrays 
liftoff is scheduled for 117 am edt nasa announced 
columbia was to have blasted off may 30 on a 9 to 10day 
astronomy mission but a leak of explosive hydrogen was detected 
during fueling and the flight was called off the leaky plumbing 
was replaced with components from the new shuttle endeavour under 
construction in california 
atlantis leak in a different spot than columbias was 
discovered in late june atlantis was rolled back to the hangar for 
repair 1 weeks ago and columbia took its place at the launch pad 
atlantis classified military mission has been rescheduled for 
november 
