factual errors in the aug 9 report by the house government 
operations committee 
the bias is clear mason said of the report 
the study said the white house ordered the study canceled after 
the federal centers for disease control said it was scientifically 
impossible to use military records to identify veterans who had 
been exposed to the defoliant 
the committee said the cdc then headed by mason did not 
document that exposure could not be assessed and disregarded 
alternate methods of measuring exposure 
