<TEXT>
the french cellist maurice gendron who played with 
internationally known stars yehudi menuhin and pablo casals died 
monday at home his family announced he was 69 
neither funeral arrangements nor cause of death were announced 
gendron was married and the father of two children 
considered one of the greatest french cellists of the century 
gendron was born in nice and took up the cello at age 12 at the 
nice conservatory 
gendron moved to paris as a teenager and captured the 
prestigious first prize in cello at the paris conservatory in 1938 
he made a name for himself playing in salons before artists like 
pablo picasso jean cocteau and francois mauriac 
gendron played for the paris symphony orchestra for more than 30 
years and performed chamber music with casals and menuhin he also 
featured as a soloist under the direction of errest ansermet 
the paris conservatory made him a professor in 1970 france also 
awarded him two of its highest civilian honors officer of the 
legion of honor and the national order of merit 
