journalists and others who fled 
kuwait after the iraqi attack told stories of wandering in the 
desert while trying to elude the invading army 
stephanie mcgehee an american stringer for the associated 
press was in a convoy of cars that fled aug 17 after britons and 
americans were ordered to gather at two kuwait hotels 
it was a hectic rather perilous drive past iraqi checkpoints 
and through uninhabited desert regions between kuwait and saudi 
arabia mcgehee of leucadia calif said by telephone from the 
khafji border post 
she and other foreigners decided to take their chances in the 
desert rather than risk becoming hostages in baghdad 
