new shows before the new season starts next month i think theyre 
trying to whip up excitement not to mention confusion 
q i have a problem with one show working it out nbc sent 
me a review cassette but now nbc says the character of gail has 
been replaced by a new actress and scenes will be reshot for air 
a so whats the problem 
q how can i review a show where the character of gail has been 
replaced by a new actress 
a just write in this performance the character of gail will 
be played by laura palmer 
q ive heard that the new network series are going to be a lot 
bolder this year particularly with the language in shows like 
raw sex and more raw sex and unsolved adulteries 
a i know what you mean i saw that unsolved adulteries 
episode where the guy says boy im sure hot martha 
q how can we warn our readers 
a just do what the networks do say portions of this show may 
not be suitable for yuppies 
q tell me again what do you say when reviewing a boring 
24part pbs series about a british spinster and a burmese doctor in 
nepal 
a you write richlytextured always compelling this is 
splendid television thats how they do it in new york 
q should we keep trying to interview bryant gumbel 
a sure but if he still says no remember that you are to keep 
referring to today as the troubled show or still mired in 
second 
q should we bother to review all those fishing shows on cable 
you know the kind where some potbellied guy talks about his hula 
popper and says whooo looks like that crappie weighs bout 10 
11 pounds easy 
a ignore those shows theyll all outdated by a new one coming 
out this fall its called bass fishing with dynamite dan 
q should we still do stories about new trends in television 
im getting tired of making up new trends in television 
a no your readers want to know about new trends in television 
particularly if theyre having trouble sleeping incidentally you 
might keep an eye on a new trend the middle east crisis has caused 
there are more middle east experts than ever before on the morning 
news shows 
q i know what you mean i saw one the other day from the center 
for strategic studies of strategic centers 
a well were just about out of time i hope youve enjoyed 
