of its companies except the four it currently operates converse 
and florsheim footwear manufacturers along with furniture makers 
lane co and broyhill industries 
that plan faltered when the subsidiaries were sold for far less 
than what the company anticipated that coupled with the collapse 
of the junkbond market left interco with more debt than it 
started with 
