<TEXT>
wholesale unleaded gasoline prices surged over 
the 1 mark for the first time monday boosted by what traders 
called a growing belief the middle east crisis will persist and 
create a longlasting tightness in supply 
anxiety over supplies also pushed prices up at the pump the 
american automobile association said its nationwide check of 
unleaded selfserve regular averaged 1237 a gallon monday up 21 
cents from a week earlier the average is 162 cents higher since 
the crisis erupted aug 2 aaa said 
the volatility that has beset oil trading over iraqs invasion 
of kuwait compelled the new york mercantile exchange to temporarily 
amend its rules monday to allow bigger daily price swings on 
oilfutures contracts 
the merc is one of the worlds leading markets for oil and 
gasoline products and is an important pacesetter for prices at the 
retail level 
unleaded gasoline for september delivery reached 1015 per 
gallon at one point during the mercs trading day monday the first 
time thats ever happened the price later settled for the day at a 
record close of 1003 per gallon an increase of 428 cents over 
fridays closing price 
west texas intermediate the benchmark us crude dipped 7 
cents per barrel to 2856 for september delivery but prices for 
later months were all up some by more than 50 cents a barrel 
more players think the crisis is going to last longer said 
annlouise hittle a senior oil analyst with shearson lehman 
brothers inc 
the market was responding partly to president bushs declaration 
that americans held in iraq and kuwait are hostages and that 
the united states holds iraq responsible she said 
some traders had predicted oil prices would drop monday on the 
news that saudi arabia promised over the weekend to boost 
production by up to 2 million barrels per day that would make up 
roughly half of the shortfall caused by the international boycott 
of oil from iraq and kuwait 
hittle said the markets might not respond to any increase in 
saudi production until they see more than verbal assurances she 
said the september contract price of crude oil might have been the 
only month to fall because traders were already starting to 
concentrate on prices for october futures with just one more day 
of trading to go on the september futures contract 
