per gallon up 242 cents from fridays close the price of natural 
gas stayed sluggish monday falling from 1440 to 1417 per 1000 
cubic feet for september delivery 
the rules change at the merc will be in effect for the next 30 
days and could only become permanent following another vote by the 
board and notification of federal regulators a merc spokeswoman 
said 
there are no limits to the movements in spot prices or the 
prices for petroleum products to be delivered in the next month 
but limits are imposed on the upward or downward movements on 
futures prices for subsequent months 
under the temporary rules the limits will be expanded by up to 
1 for crude futures and 2 cents for gasoline and home heating oil 
futures 
the limits are designed to give investors an idea of their 
potential losses when each trading day begins offering them a 
degree of protection from rapidly moving markets 
