<TEXT>
the dollar opened sharply lower against the 
japanese yen tuesday morning in tokyo as share prices quickly 
rebounded on the tokyo stock exchange 
the dollar opened at 14630 yen down 117 yen from mondays 
14747yen close 
the 225issue nikkei stock average rose 58549 points or 224 
percent to 2677596 in the first 30 minutes of early trading the 
index declined 29625 points monday closing at 2649047 
the currencys decline in early tokyo trading followed a similar 
downswing in new york the dollars drop was mainly due to active 
sales of the german mark against the yen said a bank of tokyo 
dealer who spoke on condition of anonymity 
but the dollar slowed its decline near the 146yen level because 
some investors who were reaping profits had bought at that level 
dealers said 
weakness in the german mark resulted from the collapse of the 
social democratic coalition government in east germany dealers 
said the dollar was stronger against other major currencies in new 
york 
in new york the dollar closed at 14651 yen on monday down 
from 14760 yen late friday 
traders attributed the nikkeis early strength to active buying 
by investors who had been encouraged by recovery of the yen against 
the dollar and by firm new york stocks 
