<TEXT>
donald trump has reached an agreement 
with a group representing about 60 contractors who say the 
developer owed them 60 million for work on the taj mahal 
casinohotel the creditors said monday 
the announcement was made one day before the state casino 
control commission is scheduled to rule on whether trump can use 
the taj mahal and his two other casinos as collateral for a 65 
million emergency loan trump negotiated the loan to allow him to 
make an overdue bond payment in june on the trump castle casino 
resort by the bay 
marty rosenberg a spokesman for a group of seven contractors 
negotiating with trump said an agreement had been reached but did 
not release details 
i do not have the particulars of this agreement rosenberg 
said at a news conference held at his business atlantic plate 
glass which was among the creditors 
we will be meeting with the other contractors in the near 
future he said 
trump already faces at least four lawsuits for money allegedly 
owed contractors who did roofing ornamental metal fiber glass 
and steel work on the taj mahal 
his representatives have said they are auditing all work on the 
casino to make sure it met their standards 
rosenberg indicated the negotiations had been arduous 
we have had many many meetings he said i have been in a 
rush for a long time to get this finished 
the news conference began 2 hours late as negotiators wrapped 
up the final details he said 
if youve ever dealt with donald trump you know he has his 
own timetable rosenberg said 
